====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# {{senseid|en|Q11405}}{{lb|en|woodwind instrument}} A [[woodwind]] [[instrument]] consisting of a tube with a row of holes that produce sound through vibrations caused by air blown across the edge of the holes, often tuned by plugging one or more holes with a finger; the [[Western concert flute]], a [[transverse]] [[side-blown]] flute of European origin.
#* {{RQ:Pope Works|volume=I|title=January and May|page=217|passage=The breathing '''flute's''' Å¿oft notes are heard around, / And the Å¿hril trumpets mix their Å¿ilver Å¿ound; / The vaulted roofs vvith echoing muÅ¿ic ring, / TheÅ¿e touch the vocal Å¿tops, and thoÅ¿e the trembling Å¿tring.}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|date=2008-01-15|author=w:Jon Pareles|title=To See (and Hear) the World in Five Hours: Unique Sounds Ripe for Import|work=w:The New York Times|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2008/01/15/arts/music/15webs.html
|passage=The group played huge drums placed overhead, along with '''flutes''' and a kotolike zither.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=2018|author=Robert Philip|title=The Classical Music Lover's Companion to Orchestral Music|publisher=Yale University Press|isbn=9780300120691|page=465
|passage=After another alternation of the two elements, there is a more playful episode, in  which '''flute''' and bassoon take up the first element, with swooping glissando on  the ondes Martenot.}}
# {{senseid|en|recorder}} {{lb|en|colloquial}} A [[recorder]], also a woodwind instrument.
# {{senseid|en|glass}} A [[glass]] with a long, narrow [[bowl]] and a long stem, used for drinking [[wine]], especially [[champagne]].
#* {{quote-book|en|year=2018|author=w:Sally Rooney|title=w:Normal People|chapter=Six Months Later (July  2013)|passage=These are champagne glasses, says Peggy.<br/>No, I mean the tall ones, Jamie says.<br/>You're thinking of '''flutes''', says Peggy. These are coupes.}}
# A lengthwise groove, such as one of the lengthwise grooves on a [[w:classical order|classical column]], or a groove on a cutting tool (such as a [[drill bit]], [[endmill]], or [[reamer]]), which helps to form both a cutting edge and a channel through which [[chip]]s can escape.
#: {{cot|en|q=cutter feature|tooth}}
# {{senseid|en|vertical groove}} {{lb|en|architectural element|firearms}} A [[semicylindrical]] vertical groove, as in a [[pillar]], in [[plait]]ed [[cloth]], or in a rifle barrel to cut down the weight.
# {{senseid|en|bread}} A long [[French]] [[bread roll]], [[baguette]].<ref>{{R:Simmonds Trade}}</ref>
# An [[organ stop]] with a flute-like sound.
# A [[shuttle]] in [[weave|weaving]] [[tapestry]] etc.

